## Traps

- Pre-commit `check-yaml` fails on proposals with embedded colons in
  unquoted scalars (e.g. version-range strings). When archiving via
  /codify, copy from `git show HEAD:` not the working-tree file if loom
  has appended distribution metadata mid-edit.
- BUILD-repo standing rule: never push/merge without per-action approval.
  User uses "approved" / "continue" to drive the release pipeline.
- `git reset --keep HEAD~1` (not `--hard`) is correct for backing out a
  local-only commit; remote main is protected.
- `pyenv: cannot rehash` lock errors from another account's zombie procs.
  `uv` bypasses pyenv so most commands still work.
